TY  - JOUR
TI  - Global Games and Equilibrium Selection
AU  - Carlsson, Hans
AU  - van Damme, Eric
AB  - [A global game is an incomplete information game where the actual payoff structure is determined by a random draw from a given class of games and where each player makes a noisy observation of the selected game. For 2 × 2 games, it is shown that, when the noise vanishes, iterated elimination of dominated strategies in the global game forces the players to conform to Harsanyi and Selten's risk dominance criterion.]
